Bethany G. Anderson  is the Natural and Applied Sciences Archivist and Assistant Professor in the Uni-
versity Archives and a PhD candidate in the Department of History at the University of Illinois Urbana-
Champaign.  Her  research  focuses  on  histories  of  science,  anthropology,  cybernetics,  and  women  in 
science, as well as computational approaches to archives. She holds a BA in Anthropology from the Uni-
versity of Michigan, an AM in Near Eastern Art and Archaeology from the University of Chicago, and an 
MS in Information Studies from the University of Texas at Austin. Her published work has appeared in 
Archivaria, American Archivist, Journal of Open Humanities Data, Isis: A Journal of the History of Sci-
ence Society, and Collections: A Journal for Archives and Museum Professionals.
